  "body": "@cheftako and @bsalamat brought to my attention that a number of our system pods are not marked critical.  As the critical pod annotations are enabled in GCE, it is important that we are intentional about which pods are marked critical.  Looking through my local cluster created today, I see the following kube-system pods that are NOT marked critical:\r\n\r\netcd-empty-dir-cleanup-kubernetes-master (static)\r\netcd-server-events-kubernetes-master (static)\r\netcd-server-kubernetes-master (static)\r\nevent-exporter-v0.1.0-947590526-h897n (non-static)\r\nkube-addon-manager-kubernetes-master (static)\r\nkube-apiserver-kubernetes-master (static)\r\nkube-controller-manager-kubernetes-master (static)\r\nkube-scheduler-kubernetes-master (static)\r\nl7-default-backend-4019876529-14krg (non-static)\r\nl7-lb-controller-v0.9.3-kubernetes-master (static)\r\nmonitoring-influxdb-grafana-v4-2dv01 (non-static)\r\nrescheduler-v0.3.0-kubernetes-master (static)\r\n\r\nI am not sure who the owner of each of these is, and some (especially non-static) may not need to be marked critical.\r\n**Static pods that are not marked critical can be evicted or preempted, and will never be rescheduled**, so we should almost definitely mark static system pods as critical, and should at least consider marking the non-static ones as critical.\r\n\r\ncc @davidopp @dchen1107 @vishh @piosz for people who might know who the owners of each of these pods are.\r\n\r\n",
